properties.COMMENTS: One mature Sycamore in the rear garden of 17 Ashgrove Road. It is approximately 15m tall and in good condition. It has been reduced in the past.In response to a planning application at 16 Ashgrove Road (08/00506/F) a light study was carried out by Paul Kingston of K8T Ltd, B2B Dyrham Lodge, 16 Clifton Park, BS8 3BY. This study concluded that in terms of daylight availability the tree was modelled to have very little impact on the available daylight to the rooms at the rear of the building. This report is filed in the DC section at Colston 33.

properties.LABEL: T1
properties.COMMENTS: The tree is located in the front garden of the property on the boundary between 18a and 18 The Avenue, Sneyd Park. The notification has been made by the neighbour at 18 The Avenue. The owner of the tree (Mr M.Carden) has been consulted and he is happy to accept a Tree Preservation Order on the tree to prevent all branches that overhang the adjacent property being removed.  Mr Carden has pointed out some minor cracking within his property and was concerned that a TPO would prevent the removal of the tree if it were causing subsidence. I have reassured Mr Carden that providing there is reasonable justification,  ie that the ash in the balance of probability is the cause of the damage  then sufficient works which may include removal, will be allowed.
